{
  "texts": [
    "Due to the substantial volume of real-world industrial facilities, the temporal complexity of NeRF rendering hinders its implementation in realtime, stereoscopic, high-resolution, high-frame-rate industrial VR applications.",
    "Furthermore, although there are vast amount of recent work on NeRF (Barron et al., 2021; Müller et al., 2022), prior efforts have mainly concentrated on demonstrating proof-of-concept experiment results, rather than delivering a user-friendly toolkit for visualizing and interacting with real-world NeRF models in immersive VR environments.",
    "As a first step towards adapting VR NeRF to real-world industrial processes and applications, we present Magic NeRF Lens, a visualization toolkit for virtual facility inspection leveraging NeRF as photorealistic representations of complex real-world environments.",
    "Our framework provides a native render plugin that enables interoperability between a low-level network inference engine (Müller et al., 2022) and a high-level game engine (Li et al., 2022a), making customized VR NeRF experience creation possible through typical VR application development workflows using the Unity game engine.",
    "To reduce the temporal complexity of VR NeRF rendering, we introduce a data fusion technique that combines the complementary strengths of volumetric rendering and geometric rasterization."
  ]
}